        q: `A 32-year-old woman has a one-month history of chronic cough with fever. A chest radiograph shows many small, ill-defined, nodular opacities in all lung fields. A transbronchial biopsy reveals circumscribed collections of epithelioid cells as well as lymphocytes and plasma cells. This patient is most likely infected with which of the following?`,
