        q: `A 35-year-old man has a three-month history of mid-epigastric pain. An upper gastrointestinal endoscopy shows a shallow ulceration of the gastric antrum. Microscopic examination of a biopsy from the ulcer base shows an increased number of capillaries and a mononuclear cell infiltrate composed of lymphocytes, plasma cells, and macrophages. This histologic appearance is indicative of which of the following forms of inflammation?`,
