        q: `An 80-year-old man develops cough, fever with chills and rigors, and hypotension. Laboratory tests show neutrophilic leukocytosis, and blood cultures are positive for gram-negative bacteria. Despite intravenous antibiotics and supportive therapy, he dies a few days later. At autopsy, lesions similar to those illustrated in the kidneys are found in multiple organs. Microscopic examination shows liquefactive necrosis and accumulation of neutrophils. The movement of these neutrophils into the tissues is most likely to be mediated by which of the following substances?`,
