        optionFeedback: [`Activation of complement either directly by bacteria (alternative and lectin pathways) or following binding of antibodies (classical pathway) generates products, mainly C3b, that opsonize the bacteria and promote their phagocytosis by neutrophils, followed by intracellular killing.`,`Fibrin is produced during blood clotting. It is not involved in phagocytosis.`,`Kallikrein is a serine protease that cleaves precursor proteins (kininogens) in the plasma to generate active kinins such as bradykinin. These cause vasodilation, pain, smooth muscle contraction, and increased vascular permeability.`,`Plasmin is an enzyme that breaks down clots (and cleaves other plasma proteins). It is not involved in phagocytosis.`,`Thrombin is produced during blood clotting. It is not involved in phagocytosis.`],
