        ansText: `Rationale:- Activation of complement either directly by bacteria (alternative and lectin pathways) or following binding of antibodies (classical pathway) generates products, mainly C3b, that opsonize the bacteria and promote their phagocytosis by neutrophils, followed by intracellular killing.  .`,
