        optionFeedback: [`In fibrinous inflammation, a mesh of fibrin is deposited on an inflamed serosal surface (e.g., pleura, pericardium).`,`Granulomatous inflammation is a form of chronic inflammation characterized by foci of activated macrophages (granulomas).`,`Purulent inflammation contains pus, a mixture of dead bacteria, neutrophils, and devitalized tissue. It is seen in acute infections by bacteria (called pyogenic—pus-forming—bacteria).`,`Blisters (vesicles) are caused by necrosis of epithelial cells and accumulation of fluid under the dead epithelium because of locally increased vascular permeability. This type of acute inflammation is called <i>serous</i> because the yellowish fluid resembles serum.`,`An ulcer is a discontinuity in a surface epithelium, such as the skin, stomach, or duodenum.`],
